  "description": "Survey of philosophical accounts of quality, property, and condition — from Aristotle's categories through Whitehead's eternal objects to Deleuze's intensive differences. Examines competing frameworks for understanding what qualities are, how they exist, and whether reality is fundamentally constituted by stable substances bearing properties or by processes actualizing potentials.",
